===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}

{{liushu|p}}: a stomach with food inside, originally appearing as {{zh-l|*𱕻}}. A semantic {{och-l|*肉}} was added later to differentiate.

The bronze script form merely consisted of two concentric circles. An inner portion of the character was later added, namely a mutated form of the [[seal script]] character of {{zh-l|*米}} ("rice"), representing grains within the stomach (see also [[鬯]]).

The character looked like {{och-l|*𦞅}} in the small seal script. In the [[clerical script]] form, the upper component was simplified to the unrelated {{och-l|*田}} as an instance of ''{{w|libian}}'' simplification.

The ancient form of the character can be seen within the lower component of {{och-l|*𦳊}}.

